	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 18th 5:02 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>the best way of twisting i have come up with has been with hot keys playing 2 songs in a row and with two hot keys with two songs you can play 4 songs easy the way its done is <br><br>right click your hot key<br>in the first line put in /stop casting this will stop the casting of the spell thats playing at that minute so you dont have to hit it twice and if you arnt casting it wont affect anything<br>in the next line put /cast # of what ever spell you want<br>the next line put /pause 30 whichs pause's your casting of the next spell so it doesnt stop your first spell<br>and the last line put in /cast # of what ever spell you want to cast next<br><br>this has been a great way to have your casting not intrupted buy hitting a wrong key or casting at the wrong time so give it a try and see how much it helps<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
