<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99019236387211></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99019236387211><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=4&mid=99019236387211>RE: New Bard Needs Advice</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=27649><span id=Guru>Palarran</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>116 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 18th 9:26 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.31]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you can get your hands on one, a polished granite tomahawk will work well from about 10-20.  Every time the weapon procs, berserker strength will absorb the next 35 points of damage you take (and any remaining damage from the last hit before 35 points of damage are done).  When you are soloing at that level you are going to be hit a lot, unless you are doing something like bellow kiting in which case your weapons won't matter.  In a group your songs will draw a lot of attention since tanks can't yet do an overwhelming amount of damage to distract the mobs, so you'll be hit often anyway.<br><br>A silvery war axe will do more damage, 6/22 instead of 6/26, for about the same price (roughly 100pp for each) if berserker strength doesn't matter to you.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
