	   <tr><td colspan=2>At 3rd level you should use the weapons and armour you presently have.  Do not twink yourself to much because you will tend to become dependent on your fighting ablilities.  Your songs will become more and more important to you as you go up in levels.  <br><br>You say you are bored with your last class well the Bard was good choice to help you out of bordom.  Of all the classes in EQ the bard is the one you can have the most fun with in Role Playing situations.  We are the romantics, the jesters, the story tellers (truth or fabircated).  A bard who is a Bard is almost always welcomed in groups.  We Bards are your best group oriented class so take advantage of it.  We can solo but why.  Our fighting skills are just to get us by, our songs our our best weapon.  IMHO you should just enjoy the Bard class, not try to power level him/her.  Do not worry with twinking him but obtain the instruments, equipment, armour and weapons best suited for your present level.  The Bard class will drive you up the wall if you try to solo him to the always wanted next level.  It can be done and is done, but you lose so much of this class best playing by doing that.  Explore the world with your Bard and become the most valuble person in any group with your song twisting and your knowledge of Norrath.  I realize that this tends to be considered bad advise to many people, take you a year or two to obtain top levels.  If yo do your Bard is going to become your favorite character.  Bards should be played just to enjoy the gaming experience of grouping with others.  If you do not want to do a lot of grouping, but soloing then other classes are better suited for this.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
